#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.42"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.42:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.42:0.2"
msgid "5. Muṇḍarājavagga "
msgstr "5. With King Muṇḍa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.42:0.3"
msgid "42. Sappurisasutta "
msgstr "42. A Good Person "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.42:1.1"
msgid "“Sappuriso, bhikkhave, kule jāyamāno bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a good person is born in a family for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of the people. "

#. VAR: mātāpitūnaṃ → mātāpitunnaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.42:1.2"
msgid "mātāpitūnaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; "
msgstr "For the benefit, welfare, and happiness of mother and father; "

msgctxt "an5.42:1.3"
msgid "puttadārassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; "
msgstr "children and partners; "

msgctxt "an5.42:1.4"
msgid "dāsakammakaraporisassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; "
msgstr "bondservants, workers, and staff; "

msgctxt "an5.42:1.5"
msgid "mittāmaccānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; "
msgstr "friends and colleagues; "

msgctxt "an5.42:1.6"
msgid "samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti. "
msgstr "and ascetics and brahmins. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.47, sc2
msgctxt "an5.42:2.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāmegho sabbasassāni sampādento bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; "
msgstr "It’s like a great rain cloud, which nourishes all the crops for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of the people. "

msgctxt "an5.42:2.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sappuriso kule jāyamāno bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; "
msgstr "In the same way, a good person is born in a family for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of the people. … "

msgctxt "an5.42:2.3"
msgid "mātāpitūnaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.42:2.4"
msgid "puttadārassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.42:2.5"
msgid "dāsakammakaraporisassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.42:2.6"
msgid "mittāmaccānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.42:2.7"
msgid "samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hotīti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.42:3.1"
msgid "Hito bahunnaṃ paṭipajja bhoge, "
msgstr "The gods protect one who is guarded by principle, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:3.2"
msgid "Taṃ devatā rakkhati dhammaguttaṃ; "
msgstr "who uses their wealth for the welfare of the many. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:3.3"
msgid "Bahussutaṃ sīlavatūpapannaṃ, "
msgstr "One who is learned, with precepts and observances intact, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: vijahati → vijahāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.42:3.4"
msgid "Dhamme ṭhitaṃ na vijahati kitti. "
msgstr "and steady in principle, doesn’t lose their reputation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.42:4.1"
msgid "Dhammaṭṭhaṃ sīlasampannaṃ, "
msgstr "Firm in principle, accomplished in ethical conduct, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:4.2"
msgid "saccavādiṃ hirīmanaṃ; "
msgstr "truthful, conscientious, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:4.3"
msgid "Nekkhaṃ jambonadasseva, "
msgstr "like a coin of mountain gold: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:4.4"
msgid "ko taṃ ninditumarahati; "
msgstr "who is worthy of criticizing them? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:4.5"
msgid "Devāpi naṃ pasaṃsanti, "
msgstr "Even the gods praise them, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.42:4.6"
msgid "brahmunāpi pasaṃsito”ti. "
msgstr "and by Brahmā, too, they’re praised.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.42:4.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
